{"body": "@josevalim\r\n\r\nI think that `response.charset` is empty in the `charset_meta_tag` rendering time\r\nexcept we explicitly assign response.charset (a.k.a. normal case)\r\n\r\nThus, I used `charset argument`, `Content-Type`, `response.charset` and `AD::Response.default_charset` in above patch.\r\n\r\nBut, certainly, my implementation is a little complexity.\r\nFor example, do we stop arguement and Content-Type support ?\r\n\r\n```ruby\r\n      def charset_meta_tag\r\n        tag('meta', :charset => (response.charset || response.class.default_charset)).html_safe\r\n      end\r\n```", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/3050195", "created_at": "2011-12-07T17:24:41Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/3877#issuecomment-3050195", "updated_at": "2011-12-07T17:24:41Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 3877, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kennyj/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kennyj/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kennyj/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/kennyj", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kennyj/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/kennyj", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kennyj/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/1f0b221851379759360d7130dabdfa53?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F54ecc28e9508fcf28363014b0d1b4eb8.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kennyj/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kennyj/received_events", "gravatar_id": "1f0b221851379759360d7130dabdfa53", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kennyj/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "kennyj", "type": "User", "id": 13426, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kennyj/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5238304bbd3543c15100f60c"}, "id": 3050195, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/3877"}
